text: Telford Lake is a lake in Leduc, Alberta.It is home to boat races and many other events.http://www.leducboatclub.com/ ==History== Around 1890, Robert Telford, a politician from Quebec, bought a plot of land near the lake.Leduc, Alberta#History The lake was later named for him. ==Wildlife== There are many species of wildlife in the Telford Lake riverbanks. Conservation projects are numerous in Telford Lake.http://www.leduc.ca/Assets/Departments/Parks+Rec+and+Culture/Telford+Lake+Master+Plan+Final+Report.pdf ==External links== * ==References== Category:Lakes of Alberta
